<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="589" pageId="1" pageNumber="588" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1887,2019]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,572]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="589" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">
The general habitus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Acosta &amp; Guerrero" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Sorensen" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[403,594,1887,1910]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="1" pageNumber="588" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[403,594,1887,1910]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">Eusarcus minutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[602,726,1887,1911]" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[602,726,1887,1911]" pageId="1" pageNumber="588" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[742,826,1887,1911]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1742,1766]" captionTargetBox="[152,1428,1012,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-280@1.[151,1436,1008,1718]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1: Eusarcus minutus (Sørensen) comb. nov. A: Habitus in dorsal view, male from General Paz, Corrientes province, Argentina (LEA 000.422), scale 1 mm; B-C: Distal end of penis, male from Las Gamas, Santa Fe province, Argentina (MACN), B: dorsal view, C: lateral view, scale 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5026903" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5026903/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
) resembles closely most species in the genus. The main shared features include the three well-developed paracheliceral frontal apophyses, the shape and curvature of the prolateral apophysis on coxa IV of males, the triangular, short, blunt prolateral apophysis on the male trochanter IV, and male femur IV with prolateral and retrolateral rows of apophyses and two distinct ventroapical ones (
<bibRefCitation author="Hara, M. R. &amp; Pinto-da-Rocha, R." lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="589" pageId="1" pageNumber="588" pagination="1 - 136" refId="ref2681" refString="Hara, M. R. &amp; Pinto-da-Rocha, R. (2010) Systematic review and cladistic analysis of the genus Eusarcus Perty 1833 (Arachnida, Opiliones, Gonyleptidae). Zootaxa, 2698 (1), 1 - 136. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2698.1.1" type="journal article" year="2010">Hara &amp; Pinto-da-Rocha 2010</bibRefCitation>
). Unlike most 
<taxonomicName box="[369,555,151,175]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[369,467,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Eusarcus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, which typically bear a median conic apophysis on the scutal area III, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Acosta &amp; Guerrero" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Sorensen" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[1321,1436,152,175]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis box="[1321,1436,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">E. minutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks any armature on the scutum, a feature shared with a few other species, like 
<emphasis box="[1014,1053,188,211]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">e.g.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Hara &amp; Pinto-da-Rocha, 2010" authorityName="Hara" authorityYear="2010" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sergipanus">
<emphasis box="[1059,1205,188,211]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">E. sergipanus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hara, M. R. &amp; Pinto-da-Rocha, R." pageId="2" pageNumber="589" pagination="1 - 136" refId="ref2681" refString="Hara, M. R. &amp; Pinto-da-Rocha, R. (2010) Systematic review and cladistic analysis of the genus Eusarcus Perty 1833 (Arachnida, Opiliones, Gonyleptidae). Zootaxa, 2698 (1), 1 - 136. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2698.1.1" type="journal article" year="2010">Hara &amp; Pinto-da-Rocha, 2010</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Mello-Leitao, 1931)" baseAuthorityName="Mello-Leitao" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[266,644,223,248]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gemignanii">
<emphasis box="[266,282,224,247]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[294,414,224,247]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">gemignanii</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mello-Leitao, C. F. de" box="[427,636,223,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" pagination="83 - 97" refId="ref2866" refString="Mello-Leitao, C. F. de (1931) Notas sobre arachnideos argentinos. Annaes da Academia Brasileira de Ciencias, 3 (2), 83 - 97." type="journal article" year="1931">Mello-Leitão, 1931</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Ringuelet, 1955)" baseAuthorityName="Ringuelet" baseAuthorityYear="1955" box="[693,1059,223,247]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uruguayensis">
<emphasis box="[693,709,224,247]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[722,864,224,247]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">uruguayensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ringuelet, R. A." box="[877,1051,223,247]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" pagination="279 - 297" refId="ref2954" refString="Ringuelet, R. A. (1955) Noticias sobre opiliones del Uruguay. Notas del Museo de La Plata, Zoologia, 18 (163), 279 - 297." type="journal article" year="1955">Ringuelet, 1955</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. In addition, the ocular mound of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Acosta &amp; Guerrero" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Sorensen" baseAuthorityYear="1884" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">E. minutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is armed by a single apophysis (
<figureCitation box="[586,670,259,284]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1742,1766]" captionTargetBox="[152,1428,1012,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-280@1.[151,1436,1008,1718]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1: Eusarcus minutus (Sørensen) comb. nov. A: Habitus in dorsal view, male from General Paz, Corrientes province, Argentina (LEA 000.422), scale 1 mm; B-C: Distal end of penis, male from Las Gamas, Santa Fe province, Argentina (MACN), B: dorsal view, C: lateral view, scale 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5026903" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5026903/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
), instead of the paired armature most frequent in genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1833" box="[1270,1368,260,283]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1270,1368,260,283]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Eusarcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hara, M. R. &amp; Pinto-da-Rocha, R." pageId="2" pageNumber="589" pagination="1 - 136" refId="ref2681" refString="Hara, M. R. &amp; Pinto-da-Rocha, R. (2010) Systematic review and cladistic analysis of the genus Eusarcus Perty 1833 (Arachnida, Opiliones, Gonyleptidae). Zootaxa, 2698 (1), 1 - 136. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2698.1.1" type="journal article" year="2010">Hara &amp; Pinto-da-Rocha 2010</bibRefCitation>
). The referred character states were used by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ringuelet, R. A." box="[892,1075,295,319]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" pagination="127 - 439" refId="ref2987" refString="Ringuelet, R. A. (1959) Los aracnidos argentinos del orden Opiliones. Revista del Museo Argentino de Ciencias Naturales Bernardino Rivadavia, Ciencias Zoologicas, 5 (2), 127 - 439, pls. I - XX." type="journal article" year="1959">Ringuelet (1959)</bibRefCitation>
to separate 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sorensen" authorityYear="1895" box="[1205,1297,295,319]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Pucrolia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1205,1297,295,319]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Pucrolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1833" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Eusarcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The tarsal formula 5-6-6-6 of the nominal genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sorensen" authorityYear="1895" box="[732,824,331,355]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Pucrolia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[732,824,331,355]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Pucrolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(of little help) is shared with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mello-Leitao" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[1150,1300,332,355]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gemignanii">
<emphasis box="[1150,1166,332,355]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1180,1300,332,355]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">gemignanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="H. Soares, 1966" authorityName="H. Soares" authorityYear="1966" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grumani">
<emphasis box="[1315,1331,332,355]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1346,1436,332,355]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">grumani</emphasis>
H. 
<bibRefCitation author="Soares, H. E. M." box="[184,321,367,392]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" pagination="87 - 102" refId="ref3247" refString="Soares, H. E. M. (1966) Opilioes da colecao Gofferje (Opiliones: Gonyleptidae, Phalangodidae). Papeis Avulsos do Departamento de Zoologia, Sao Paulo, 18 (10), 87 - 102." type="journal article" year="1966">Soares, 1966</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ringuelet" baseAuthorityYear="1955" box="[372,544,368,391]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uruguayensis">
<emphasis box="[372,388,368,391]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[402,544,368,391]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">uruguayensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Finally, the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Acosta &amp; Guerrero" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Sorensen" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[868,1056,368,391]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis box="[868,1056,368,391]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Eusarcus minutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1071,1183,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1742,1766]" captionTargetBox="[152,1428,1012,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-280@1.[151,1436,1008,1718]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1: Eusarcus minutus (Sørensen) comb. nov. A: Habitus in dorsal view, male from General Paz, Corrientes province, Argentina (LEA 000.422), scale 1 mm; B-C: Distal end of penis, male from Las Gamas, Santa Fe province, Argentina (MACN), B: dorsal view, C: lateral view, scale 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5026903" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5026903/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Fig. 1B–C</figureCitation>
) consistently match the descriptions of those of most 
<taxonomicName box="[466,648,403,427]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[466,564,404,427]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Eusarcus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis box="[663,690,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">cf.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hara, M. R. &amp; Pinto-da-Rocha, R." box="[696,1014,403,428]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" pagination="1 - 136" refId="ref2681" refString="Hara, M. R. &amp; Pinto-da-Rocha, R. (2010) Systematic review and cladistic analysis of the genus Eusarcus Perty 1833 (Arachnida, Opiliones, Gonyleptidae). Zootaxa, 2698 (1), 1 - 136. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2698.1.1" type="journal article" year="2010">Hara &amp; Pinto-da-Rocha 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="589" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,572]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">
As for the largely questioned 
<emphasis box="[523,737,439,463]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Roewer" authorityYear="1913" box="[523,733,439,463]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Pucrolia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilipes">Pucrolia gracilipes</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
it is to be considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Acosta &amp; Guerrero" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Sorensen" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[1210,1326,440,463]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis box="[1210,1326,440,463]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">E. minutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[1390,1436,440,464]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">type</typeStatus>
material of the former is presumably lost (
<bibRefCitation author="Guariento, L. A. &amp; Bonvicini, M. C. &amp; Ballarin, L. &amp; Devincenzo, U. &amp; Gardini, G. &amp; Moretto, E. &amp; Pantini, P. &amp; Nicolosi, P." box="[594,824,475,500]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" pagination="36 - 41" refId="ref2585" refString="Guariento, L. A., Bonvicini, M. C., Ballarin, L., Devincenzo, U., Gardini, G., Moretto, E., Pantini, P. &amp; Nicolosi, P. (2018) Giovanni Canestrini's heritage at the Zoology Museum of Padova University (Italy): a rediscovery of his arachnological collections and described species. Arachnologische Mitteilungen / Arachnology Letters, 55 (1), 36 - 41. https: // doi. org / 10.30963 / aramit 5506" type="journal article" year="2018">
Guariento 
<emphasis box="[709,762,475,499]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
), but drawings and description given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Canestrini, G." pageId="2" pageNumber="589" pagination="100 - 111" refId="ref2547" refString="Canestrini, G. (1888) Intorno ad alcuni Acari ed Opilionidi dell' America. Atti della Societa Veneto-Trentina di Scienze Naturali, Padova, Series 1, 11 (1), 100 - 111." type="journal article" year="1888">Canestrini (1888: 107</bibRefCitation>
, Pl. 9, figs. 4, 4a-d) clearly show a female 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Acosta &amp; Guerrero" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Sorensen" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[642,755,512,535]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis box="[642,755,512,535]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">E. minutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[815,861,512,536]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Roewer" authorityYear="1913" box="[981,1114,511,535]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Pucrolia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilipes">
<emphasis box="[981,1114,511,535]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">P. gracilipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Resistencia, 
<collectingRegion box="[1262,1432,511,535]" country="Argentina" name="Chaco" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Chaco province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,259,547,571]" name="Argentina" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Argentina</collectingCountry>
) is placed in middle of the geographic range of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Acosta &amp; Guerrero" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Sorensen" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[770,883,548,571]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis box="[770,883,548,571]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">E. minutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis box="[899,926,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">cf.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ringuelet, R. A." box="[932,1099,547,571]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" pagination="127 - 439" refId="ref2987" refString="Ringuelet, R. A. (1959) Los aracnidos argentinos del orden Opiliones. Revista del Museo Argentino de Ciencias Naturales Bernardino Rivadavia, Ciencias Zoologicas, 5 (2), 127 - 439, pls. I - XX." type="journal article" year="1959">Ringuelet 1959</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
